Police in Ekiti has launched a manhunt for the killers of a poultry farmer in Ado-Ekiti. The Police Public Relations ASP Sunday Abutu, while confirming the incident said the deceased was murdered right in front of his farm situated at a Farmstead Ago Aduloju. He said “A distress call was received yesterday being 09/03/2022 at about 18:30hrs by Odo Ado division that a man was shot by two unidentified gunmen right in front of his poultry farm at Ago Adeloju area. Katsina: Police, Other Security Agencies To Collaborate Against… Police Foil Attack, Recover Arms, Ammunition In Kaduna ” A team of police personnel moved to the scene where the victim was met in the pool of his blood. “He was immediately rushed to the hospital where he was confirmed dead by a medical doctor. He said Investigation had commenced to unravel the identities of the perpetrators, arrest and bring them to book. Independent learnt that certain unknown assailants had besieged his residence earlier when he was away to a night vigil. A source said the deceased farmer had just finished the day’s work on his farm and had stepped into his vehicle, he was about to settle in, when he was shot on the head at a close range by his assailants. POLL His lifeless body was discovered in the pool of his own blood in the vehicle, while his assailants disappeared into thin air.